The selection panel for the appointment of five TSC members has shortlisted 35 candidates. The panel chairperson Thomas Koyier said the applicants will be interviewed on the dates indicated and should report 30 minutes before the interview time. The exercise will take place at Harambee House. The applicants are required to bring their National Identity Card/Passport, academic and professional certificates and any other supporting document and testimonials. They will also be required to bring clearance certificates from the KRA, Helb, Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission, Credit Reference Bureau and police clearance from the DCI. “Members of the public are hereby invited to submit memoranda (if any) on the above-shortlisted applicants to the chairperson of the selection panel not later than July 19, at 5:00 pm,” Koyier said.  Edited by Kiilu Damaris